  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed; all credibility factors are assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels. Wide uncertainty bounds on hemolysis predictions are documented honestly, with explicit sensitivity analysis identifying the dominant uncertain inputs. Decision: Accepted with documented residual uncertainty acknowledged in the offset rationale.",
