  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/sensitivity/morrison-cou2-mc-sensitivity",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Monte Carlo Sobol sensitivity analysis — hemolysis index drivers",
    "description": "A 10 000-sample Monte Carlo Sobol sensitivity analysis was performed varying six uncertain inputs: blood viscosity (±8%), power-law hemolysis exponent C (±15%), turbulent stress exposure time (±20%), inlet velocity profile shape (±12%), wall shear stress scaling coefficient (±10%), and mesh resolution parameter (±5%). First-order Sobol indices identify the hemolysis power-law exponent C and turbulent stress exposure time as the two dominant drivers, jointly accounting for 71% of output variance in predicted hemolysis index; the remaining four inputs contribute less than 10% individually. These wide bounds on C and exposure time are the primary source of the ±38% prediction interval on absolute hemolysis index and are documented as residual uncertainty in the decision record."
  },
